<br><br>
Average temperatures for 2017 (Figure 7, middle panels) were higher than climatological values for 1981-2010 over virtually all of Europe. Temperatures were particularly above average over Svalbard, northern Russia, Spain, Portugal and the Ukraine. The E-OBS dataset also gives high values over parts of south-eastern Europe; values from the ERA-Interim dataset are less exceptional there, though well-above average.
<br><br>
The analysis of the maximum (usually daytime) and minimum (usually night-time) temperatures (Figure 7, top and bottom panel) observed each day shows that both temperatures were higher in 2017 than their 1981-2010 average over almost all of the European region covered by the analysis. Maximum temperatures were particularly high in the south, and minimum temperatures were more anomalous in the north.
