<h3 id="indextemp">Climate Indicators</h3>
The number of frost days, days with minimum temperature below 0&#176;C (Figure 9), was below the average number of days for the 1981-2010 reference period for large parts of Europe. A central band of Europe had about 30 frost days less than normal. Only large parts of Scandinavia, the Alps and small regions in southern France, Spain and Portugal experienced more frost days than normal.
