<h3 id="indexprecip">Climate Indicators</h3>
The number of rainy days, days where the daily precipitation is at least 1 mm (Figure 15), shows the arid conditions over most of Spain and Portugal, the Cote d͛'Azur and much of Italy. The deviation of the number of rainy days from the long-term (1981-2010) mean shows that the area with less rainy days than usual extends beyond this arid region and covers the Iberian peninsula, France and large parts of the area between the Adriatic and the Black Sea.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rr1_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RR1_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rr1_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RR1_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
