<br><br>
<em>Figure 17: R20mm: Number of days with daily precipitation exceeding 20 mm in 2017 (left) and anomaly w.r.t. 1981-2010 (right). E-OBS v16.0e</em>
<br><br>
<a href="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RX1day_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RX1day_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_2017_year_v16_0e_nc__2017-07-01T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_2017_year_v16_0e_nc__2017-07-01T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_anom_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RX1day_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_anom_2017_year_v16_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_RX1day_baselayers_overlay_2017-07-01T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_anom_2017_year_v16_0e_nc__2017-07-01T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/2017/Stateofclimate_2017_rx1day_anom_2017_year_v16_0e_nc__2017-07-01T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 18: RX1day: Highest 1-day precipitation amount in 2017 (left) and anomaly w.r.t. 1981-2010 (right). E-OBS v16.0e</em>
<br><br>
However, the fraction of annual precipitation due to very wet days (relating to the locally defined 95th percentile, Figure 19) shows generally positive values over Europe, with the largest values along the Norwegian Atlantic coast, around the Baltic states and in south eastern Europe. Positive values of this index indicate that the distribution of daily precipitation changes towards a more extreme distribution.
<br><br>
